Survey/Quiz Title: Introductory Survey for Automated Design Decision Support Software for Productive Indoor Environment
Question:
AUTOMATED DESIGN DECISION SUPPORT SYSTEM FOR PRODUCTIVE INDOOR ENVIRONMENT


Information Flow Map:
Step 1- Create the required building model in Revit.
Step 2- Export Building Information Modelling (BIM) model to Indoor Environment Quality (IEQ) software.
Step 3- Trained Artificial Neural Network (ANN) (pre-developed) model is connected to Indoor Environment Quality (IEQ) software.
Step 4- The trained model provides output from a scale of 1-5, giving insight to whether the designed building’s indoor environment will have a positive impact on occupant productivity.
Step 5- Designers can use this feedback to ensure maximum productivity for occupants.

 

17a. Is the proposed information flow model simple to understand?
